INSERT INTO `checks` VALUES (1,'img','Known',5,'','All <code>img</code> elements have an <code>alt</code> attribute.','<code>img</code> element missing <code>alt</code> attribute.','All <code>img</code> elements must have an <code>alt</code> attribute.','All images must have alternate text. It\'s required by people that are unable to view the image.','Add an <code>alt</code> attribute to your <code>img</code> element.','<img src=\"rex.jpg\" alt=\"a picture of Rex the cat\" />','','',''),(2,'img','Likely',6,'covered by test 6','Alt text is not the same as the filename unless author has confirmed it is correct.','Image has suspicious Alt text (same as filename).','<code>img</code> element cannot have <code>alt</code> attribute value that is the same as its <code>src</code> attribute.','Alt text should describe the image. This Alt text is suspicious because it may be just placeholder text.','','','Is this Alt text appropriate for the image?','Alt text is appropriate for the image.','Alt text is not appropriate for the image.'),(3,'img','Likely',5,'','Image Alt text is short.','Image Alt text may be too long.','Image Alt text is short or user must confirm that Alt text is as short as possible.','Alt text should be as short as possible.','','','Is this Alt text as short as possible?','Alt text is as short as possible.','Alt text is not as short as possible.'),(4,'img','Likely',6,'covered by test 178','Non-Decorative images must have Alt text.','Image has suspicious Alt text (empty string \"\").','<code>img</code> element cannot have <code>alt</code> attribute value of null (\"\") if WIDTH and HEIGHT attribute values are both greater than 25.','All images require a text equivalent (Alt text) but you should set the Alt text to null (\"\") for decorative images. This image has null Alt text but does not appear to be a decorative image.','','','Is this a decorative image that requires null Alt text?','Image is decorative (null Alt text is OK).','Image is not decorative (null Alt text is not OK).'),(5,'img','Likely',1,'','Important images should not have spacer Alt text.','Image has suspicious Alt text (all spaces).','<code>img</code> element cannot have <code>alt</code> attribute value of whitespace if WIDTH and HEIGHT attribute values are both greater than 25.','All images require a text equivalent (Alt text) but you may set the Alt text to all spaces (\"  \") for decorative images. This image has spacer Alt text but does not appear to be a decorative image.','','','Is this a decorative image that requires spacer Alt text?','Image is decorative (spacer Alt text is OK).','Image is not decorative (spacer Alt text is not OK).'),(6,'img','Likely',4,'accepted by group but still need to define placeholder text','Alt text for all <code>img</code> elements is not placeholder text unless author has confirmed it is correct.','Image has suspicious Alt text (placeholder text).','<code>img</code> element cannot have <code>alt</code> attribute value of \"nbsp\" or \"spacer\".','The alternate (ALT) text for this image is suspicious because it appears to be \"placeholder\" text.','','','Is the Alt text appropriate for the image?','Alt text is appropriate for the image.','Alt text is not appropriate for the image.'),(7,'img','Known',6,'covered by tests 174 and 197','Alt text for all <code>img</code> elements used as source anchors is not empty when there is no other text in the anchor.','Image used as anchor is missing valid Alt text.','<code>img</code> element cannot have <code>alt</code> attribute value of null or whitespace if the <code>img</code> element is contained by an A element and there is no other link text.','If an image is used as a link then it must have alternate (ALT) text that describes the link destination. The Alt text can\'t be null or all spaces.','Add Alt text that identifies the purpose or function of the image.','','','',''),(8,'img','Potential',5,'','A long description is used for each <code>img</code> element that does not have Alt text conveying the same information as the image.','<code>img</code> element may require a long description.','<code>img</code> element must contain a <code>longdesc</code> attribute.','Complex images require a long description if the image is not described within the document. If the image does require a long description, then create the description file and link to it using the <code>longdesc</code> attribute.','','','Does this image require a long description and if so is the long description properly marked?','Image does not require a long description or a long description is provided.','Image requires a long description and is not properly marked.'),(9,'img','Known',5,'contentious - should review','All <code>img</code> elements that have a <code>longdesc</code> attribute also have an associated \'d-link\'.','IMG missing d-link.','<code>img</code> element that contains a <code>longdesc</code> attribute must have a following d-link. A d-link must consist of an A element that contains only the text \"d\" or \"D\". The A element must have an <code>href</code> attribute that is a valid URI and is the same as the <code>img</code> element\'s <code>longdesc</code> attribute. The d-link must immediately follow the <code>img</code> element, separated only by whitespace.','D-links are required until there is more browser support for the <code>longdesc</code> attribute.','Immediately following the image, add an anchor that links to your long description file. The text of the anchor should be the letter \'d\'.','','','',''),(10,'img','Potential',3,'review postponed until we develop a test for flicker','All <code>img</code> elements have associated images that do not flicker.','Image (GIF) may flicker.','This error is generated for all <code>img</code> elements that contain a <code>src</code> attribute value that ends with \".gif\" (case insensitive). and have a width and height larger than 25.','People with photosensitive epilepsy can have seizures triggered by flickering or flashing in the 4 to 59 flashes per second (Hertz) range with a peak sensitivity at 20 flashes per second as well as quick changes from dark to light (like strobe lights).','','','Does this image flicker?','Image does not flicker.','Image does flicker.'),(11,'img','Potential',5,'','Alt text for all <code>img</code> elements contains all text in the image unless the image text is decorative or appears elsewhere in the document.','Image may contain text that is not in Alt text.','This error is generated for all <code>img</code> elements that have a width and height greater than 50.','','','','Is any text within the image also in the Alt text (unless text is decorative or redundant)?','Any text in image is also in Alt text or text in image is decorative or redundant.','Image contains some text that is not in Alt text.'),(12,'img','Known',6,'if using ismap then should not use usemap','All <code>img</code> elements with an <code>ismap</code> attribute have a valid <code>usemap</code> attribute.','Server-side image map used without client-side image map.','<code>img</code> element may not contain an <code>ismap</code> attribute.','','Create a client-side image map that duplicates the functionality of the server-side image map.','','','',''),(13,'img','Known',5,'','All links in all client side image-maps are duplicated within the document.','Client-side image map missing duplicate text links.','<code>img</code> element must not contain a <code>usemap</code> attribute unless all links in the MAP are duplicated within the document. The MAP element is referred by the USEMAP element\'s <code>usemap</code> attribute. Links within MAP are referred by <code>area</code> elements <code>href</code> attribute contained by MAP element. [Editor\'s Note - can duplicate links appear anywhere within content or must they be part of a link group?]','Some people may not be able to access the links that are part of an image map. They require a duplicate set of links.','For each <code>area</code> element in an image-map, provide an equivalent anchor on the page. The anchor must have an <code>href</code> attribute set to the same value as the <code>area</code> element\'s <code>href</code> attribute. The anchor\'s text should be the same as the <code>area</code> element\'s Alt text.','','','',''),(14,'img','Potential',5,'','For all <code>img</code> elements, text does not refer to the image by color alone.','Image may be using color alone.','This error is generated for all <code>img</code> elements that have a width and height greater than 100.','You should not describe an image, or part of an image, using color alone. For example, when referring to a photograph, you should not say \"my son is wearing a red coat\". Instead say \"my son is third from the left wearing a red coat\".','','','Are there any references to this image using color alone?','There are no references to this image using color alone.','There is a reference to this image using color alone.'),(15,'img','Potential',6,'covered by tests 174 and 197','Alt text for all <code>img</code> elements used as source anchors identifies the destination of the link.','Alt text may not identify the link destination.','<code>img</code> element that is contained by an <code>a</code> (anchor) element must have Alt text that identifies the link destination.','','','','Does the Alt text for this image identify the link destination.','Alt text identifies the link destination.','Alt text does not identify the link destination.'),(16,'img','Potential',5,'','Alt text for all <code>img</code> elements is the empty string (\"\") if the image is decorative.','Alt text is not empty and image may be decorative.','Decorative images must have empty string (\"\") Alt text.','','','','Is this image decorative?','Image is not decorative.','Image is decorative.'),(17,'a','Potential',1,'','Sound file must have a text transcript.','Sound file may be missing text transcript.','<code>a</code> (anchor) element cannot con